==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fucus
<hw>Fu"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fuci</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. rock lichen, orchil, used
as a red dye, red or purple color, disguise, deceit.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A paint; a dye; also, false show.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of tough, leathery
seaweeds, usually of a dull brownish green color; rockweed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Formerly most marine alg⟦ae⟧ were called
<xex>fuci</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fucusol</ent>⟦br⟧
